'''Michel Aebischer''' (born 6 January 1997) is a Swiss professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[defensive midfielder]] for {{Italian football updater|Pisa}} club [[Pisa SC|Pisa]], on loan from [[Bologna FC 1909|Bologna]], and the [[Switzerland national football team|Switzerland national team]].<ref name="soccerway">{{Soccerway|michel-aebischer/459532}}</ref>

== Club career ==
Aebischer is a youth exponent from [[BSC Young Boys|Young Boys]]. He made his [[Swiss Super League]] debut on 10 September 2016 against [[FC Luzern|Luzern]].<ref name="soccerway2">{{cite web|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2016/09/10/switzerland/super-league/bsc-young-boys-bern/fc-luzern/2243212/|title=BSC Young Boys vs. Luzern - 10 September 2016 - Soccerway|publisher=soccerway.com|accessdate=13 October 2016}}</ref>

He was part of the Young Boys squad that won the [[2017–18 Swiss Super League]], their first league title for 32 years.<ref>{{cite web | url = https://www.reuters.com/article/ampuk-soccer-swiss/soccer-young-boys-end-32-year-wait-for-swiss-title-and-end-basel-dominance-idUKKBN1HZ0YS | title = Soccer - Young Boys end 32-year wait for Swiss title and end Basel dominance | website = Reuters | date = 28 April 2018 | access-date = 30 April 2018}}</ref>

On 25 January 2022, he joined [[Bologna FC 1909|Bologna]] in Italy. The transfer was initially a loan with a future obligation to buy the rights permanently.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=[[Bologna F.C. 1909|Bologna]]|url=https://www.bolognafc.it/aebischer-al-bologna/|title=Aebischer al Bologna|date=25 January 2022|access-date=25 January 2022|language=it}}</ref>

On 3 August 2025, Aebischer was loaned by [[Pisa SC|Pisa]], with a conditional obligation to buy.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=Pisa SC|url=https://pisasportingclub.com/en/michel-aebischer-e-del-pisa/|title=Michel Aebischer è del Pisa!|trans-title=Michel Aebischer is at Pisa!|date=3 August 2025|access-date=4 August 2025|language=it}}</ref>

==International career==
Aebischer made his debut for [[Switzerland national football team|Switzerland national team]] on 18 November 2019 in a [[UEFA Euro 2020 qualifying Group D|Euro 2020 qualifier]] against [[Gibraltar national football team|Gibraltar]]. He came on as a substitute for [[Ruben Vargas]] in the 85th minute.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=[[UEFA]]|url=https://www.uefa.com/european-qualifiers/match/2026000--gibraltar-vs-switzerland/|title=Gibraltar v Switzerland game report|date=18 November 2019}}</ref> On 9 November 2022, he was called up for the Swiss squad for the [[2022 FIFA World Cup]] in Qatar,<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.football.ch/sfv/nationalteams/a-team/news/murat-yakin-gibt-schweizer-wm-aufgebot-bekannt.aspx |title=Murat Yakin gibt Schweizer WM-Aufgebot bekannt |trans-title=Murat Yakin announces Swiss World Cup squad |publisher=[[Swiss Football Association]] |date=9 November 2022 |access-date=9 November 2022 |language=de}}</ref> where he made one appearance as a 76th-minute substitute for [[Djibril Sow]] in the 1–0 [[2022 FIFA World Cup Group G|Group G]] loss to [[Brazil national football team|Brazil]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/63698283|title= Brazil 1-0 Switzerland: Casemiro winner seals last-16 spot|date=27 November 2022|access-date=16 June 2024|website=BBC Sport}}</ref>

On 7 June 2024, Aebischer was named in the 26-man squad for the [[UEFA Euro 2024]].<ref>{{cite news |date=7 June 2024 |title=Männer-Nationalteam: Das EM-Kader steht – Zeqiri reist nicht nach Deutschland |trans-title=Men's national team: The European Championship squad is set – Zeqiri will not travel to Germany |url=https://www.football.ch/sfv/nationalteams/a-team/news/maenner-nationalteam-das-em-kader-steht-zeqiri-reist-nicht-nach-deutschland.aspx |language=de |publisher=[[Swiss Football Association]] |access-date=7 June 2024}}</ref> On 15 June, he scored his first international goal and provided an assist in a 3–1 victory over [[Hungary national football team|Hungary]] in Switzerland's opening match of the tournament.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://apnews.com/article/hungary-switzerland-euro-2024-168f7a1e4eb75bce53a3a74cdc7eb15e |title=Switzerland holds on to beat Hungary 3-1 at Euro 2024 |publisher=AP News |date=15 June 2024 }}</ref>

